</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 520<br> <font color=#333333>(4/5/02 7:49:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1191.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Who knows...</span><hr size=1> It seems that most guilds have their mages make mod rods.  However, in most cases they're just a waste of mana.  If you hand out enough rods so every cleric and wizard gets an extra 20m, and they all end the fight with more than 20m, or even close to 20m, you've done nothing in the fight.<br>
<br>
However, it isn't as simple as &quot;this fight requires rods&quot; and &quot;this fight does not.&quot;  For me, I never needed to supply more rods than pre-fight rods until Tunare and AoW (even for Vulak).  Tunare, because she's Lure-only and there's nothing else to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   AoW because the clerics spend massive amounts of mana.  By the sound of it, Seru will join that list too.  In every other fight I primarely nuke, and only supply battle-rods when I get a tell for one.  The only exception being Creator, in which case I nuke ~5 times, drop 2-3 rods, nuke, rod, etc.  <br>
<br>
Even those don't stay constant.  Tonight when we killed AoW I was able to nuke quite a bit, which I had never done before, dropped a lot of rods, and at the end of the fight I still had ~30m.  Next time I'll just nuke even more.  As our clerics get more mana, the guild gets better DPS, etc, I'll spend less on rods and more on nukes.  While I may not have had to till Tunare/AoW, your guild might be different, /points at Jaytee's example of KT.  Or maybe you should look over the fights you're doing and decide if the mod rod mana is even getting used. <p>~~
