<br>
Disappointed? I'm not sure I would go that far. It was a great adventure (my first &quot;real&quot; ToV kill) and I thoroughly enjoyed myself.<br>
<br>
It was a bit of a shock, however, to realise that at the end of the day, when it came time to nail the Dragon, the best thing I could do was to give my mana to others. As I have said here before, I think that Trans Rods are a wonderful spall and a great utility.<br>
<br>
I just don't happen to think that after 60 levels and two and a half years in Norrath that when it finally comes to challenging the Gods and slaying the masters of Dragonkind, that my class-defining role should be my ability to give Clerics and Wizards my mana.<br>
<br>
I am a Magician. I blow stuff up, and unleash Bober on unsuspecting victims. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> When I rolled up my Magician Modulation Rods didn't exist.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Quite simply, its not what I signed on to do. <p><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26251">Hogfather</A></b><P>
